AGI - An Olympic Truce in Ukraine would play the enemy and is another sign of an "absurd situation in which the West is afraid that Russia will lose war". In an interview with France Presse, the Ukrainian president, Volodymyr Zelensky>, rejects the proposal of Paris and paventa that the recent assault of Russian land to the Kharkiv region, from which 10 thousand people were evacuated, is only the first step of a wider offensive.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The Moscow offensive "may consist of different waves. There was the first wave," said Zelensky, adding that Russian troops "want to attack (but) understand that (attach) Kharkiv is very difficult". The Ukrainian president also underlined that his country needs more than one hundred planes to counter Russian air power by pointing out that Ukraine has only a quarter of the air defenses it needs? "Today we have about 25% of what we need to defend Ukraine. I'm talking about air defense. As for the planes... For Russia not to have air superiority, our fleet should have 120 to 130 modern aircraft." But the Ukrainian army would also need more men: "We need staff for reservations - admitted Zelensky -. A large number of brigades are empty. We have to do this so that the boys have a normal rotation. So their morale will improve."
&nbsp;
A new mobilization law has just entered into force to repopulate the ranks of the army. According to the Ukrainian leader, then, Russia does not have the means to launch a new major assault in Kiev while Moscow is at the offensive in eastern and north-eastern Ukraine: "They have no strength for a major offense on capital as at the beginning of the invasion," said Zelensky, who believes that the Donbass (east) and Kharkiv (north-east) are the main objectives of the Kremlin.&nbsp;
<h2> China is involved in the peace conference
Zelensky criticized the West for prohibiting Ukraine from using weapons supplied by Europe and the United States to hit the Russian territory. "They can strike us from their territory, this is the greatest advantage of Russia, and we can do nothing to their systems (arms) located on the Russian territory with Western weapons. We do not have the right," said the Ukrainian leader, stressing that he complained about this with the US Secretary of State, Antony Blinken>, this week. Zelensky then rejected the appeal of French President Emmanuel Macron> for a truce during the Paris Olympics this summer, stating that he could only help Russia move his troops and his equipment.
&nbsp;
"Tell me - I explained to Macron - who can guarantee that Russia will not use this time to bring its forces to our territory?", adding: "We are against any truce that makes the enemy's game." According to Zelensky, the Western countries that, in his opinion, support Ukraine but also have "fear" of a clear defeat of Moscow: "We are in an absurd situation where the West is afraid that Russia will lose war. And he doesn't want Ukraine to lose it," he added. Zelensky would like to see China "involved" in the peace conference in Ukraine, which Switzerland should organize in June, without Russia: "I would like to see China involved in the peace summit. Global actors, like China, have an influence on Russia. And more countries like this are on our side, on the side of the end of the war, I would say, more Russia will have to count on us," he concluded.&nbsp;

