AGI - Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky, in an exclusive interview granted to AFP, spoke about the challenges Ukraine faces in these next, delicate, months, touching more topics: a new Russian attack, Western aid, the shortage of men, the Olympic truce, the invitation to China to participate in the peace summit... But here's what the Ukrainian leader said.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h3> Russian offensive against Kharkiv</h3>
“They launched their operation, which could consist of different waves. And this is the first wave. But the situation is under control after this first wave. The Russians are no more than 5-10 kilometers from the border and we stopped them. I would not say that it is a great success (Russian), but we must be sober and admit that it is them, not us, to push in our territory. This is their advantage.”
&nbsp;
“Russia wants to conquer the city of Kharkiv, but knows it is a difficult battle. They want to attack. They understand that we have forces and will fight for a long time. But in my opinion, millions will not die to conquer Kharkiv.”
&nbsp;
<h3>No force to attack Kiev</h3>
“The Russians have no strength for a large-scale offensive on the capital as at the beginning of the invasion.”
&nbsp;
<h3> The battle of the skies
“Today we have 25% of what it takes to defend Ukraine, and I talk about air defense systems. Can we have three billions to buy two (Patriot systems) for the Kharkiv region, so that bombs no longer fall on our soldiers?”. “120, 130 F-16 or other modern aircraft: in total, we need this fleet of so many F-16s to achieve equality with Russia.”
&nbsp;
<h3>Replace ranks </h3>
“We must set up reserves. There is a significant number of brigades that are empty. We have to do this so that the boys (who are at the front) can have normal rotations. That's how morale will improve.
&nbsp;
<h3>No summer break during the Paris Olympics
“I said: Emmanuel (Macron, French President, ndr), we do not believe. Let us imagine for a moment that there is a ceasefire. First, we don't trust Putin. Second, he won't withdraw his troops. Third, (...) tell me Emmanuel - I said - who guarantees that Russia will not take advantage of it to bring its troops to our territory? We are against a truce that would make the enemy’s game.”
&nbsp;
<h3>Appeal to China</h3>
Chinese leaders “live with the feeling that if Russia loses war, it is not a loss for Russia, but a victory for the United States. So for them it is neither a victory for Ukraine nor a loss for Russia. It's a victory for the West. And they want to find a balance between the two things. That is why I would like China to participate in the peace summit of 15 and 16 June in Switzerland.
&nbsp;
<h3> West is afraid
“We are in an absurd situation where the West is afraid that Russia will lose war. And (at the same time) does not want Ukraine to lose it. Because Ukraine's final victory will lead to Russia's defeat. And the final victory of Russia will lead to the defeat of Ukraine.”
&nbsp;
<h3> Western prohibition of affecting Russia
“They can strike us from their territory, this is the greatest advantage that Russia has, and we can do nothing to their systems (arms) located on the Russian territory with Western weapons. We have no right.”
